Package: builderd
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, systemd
Recommends: docker.io
Description: Builderd Multi-Tenant Build Service
 Builderd is a multi-tenant build service that converts various source types
 (Docker images, Git repositories, archives) into optimized rootfs images for
 microVM execution with comprehensive observability and tenant isolation.
 .
 Features include:
  - Multi-source build support (Docker, Git, Archive)
  - Multi-tenant architecture with isolation
  - Real-time build metrics and observability
  - OpenTelemetry integration with traces and metrics
  - ConnectRPC/protobuf-based API
  - Resource quotas and sandboxing
  - Configurable storage backends (local, S3, GCS)